@nickcammarata I think there are a lot of 40-page ideas that get buried in 300 pages of padding and published as books.

And I don’t blame the authors. The publishers are often pushing flawed or incomplete models.

I like long books, but I’d love to see a space open up for mini books like this.

@Conaw Yerkes-Dodson Law is everywhere. It’s why we really need mentors and friends.

We struggle to start new things, because we have no one to help us navigate an ocean of information.

We give up on good things, because we have no one to push us beyond what we think we can do. https://t.co/oVZ45mYxVm

@NeilShenvi I’d add “Using clear terms” to that first list.

I love Peter Kreeft’s summary of this in his book, “Socratic Logic”. There’s a section in the introduction called “All of Logic in Two Pages”.

Here’s an excerpt. https://t.co/Ks78Sieyyc
